<br>
My opinion is that we shouldn't advercate any specific type of space development, we shouldn't advercate one type of space development scenario over another.  We should instead focus on using nuclear technology to further space missions and development.  We would only be advercating that space development happen and that nuclear be used wherever it is the best system to use.  We should also only advercate peaceful uses of space for PR purposes.<br>
<br>
This way we let all the other groups actually convince people which way is the best to go.  We would just provide assistance in getting permission to use the nuclear technology when they want to go ahead with their plans.  We might even be able to co-ordinate a few groups that are trying to get nuclear technology to allow them to share the costs of it (we would be non-profit all along and our donation policy should forbid donations coming from companies involved in nuclear technology or those that will benefit from its use in space). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uzaphod4468.showPublicProfile?language=EN>zaphod4468</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 126<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(2/4/02 11:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.bbc.co.uk/cult/hitchhikers/gallery/images/100/zaphod2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Organizing...</span><hr size=1> I guess we need to type up and make available a broader mission statement, by-laws, etc. than what is currently available on the NuclearSpace.net site...<br>
